    narr:narration """This hub gathers rubric assessments of how well artifacts are *tailored to their audience*. The dominant audience is the [YC application context](narr:Assessment_Tailoring_YC) — recurring across the [overall rubric](narr:Rubric_Assess_Tailoring), the [Scarlet/Dame application](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_ScarletDame), the [YC call](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_YC_Call), and [revenue/TAM framing](narr:Assess_Tailoring_RevenueModelTAM) sourced for investors. A second cluster targets the enterprise technical buyer: the [the customer's chief architect Chief-Architect persona](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_CustomerArchitect) and the [pilot plan's tracked personas](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_PilotPlan). A third is explicitly internal/strategic — [GTM decision-making](narr:RubricAssess_Tailoring_GTM) and architecture sessions. Exemplars praised as \"highly tailored\" ([a design collaborator/Vouch context](narr:RubricAssess_Tailoring_Sample1), the customer's chief architect) sit alongside founder/operator, blog-general, and technical-product framings. Several entries close named gaps — the [dual-persona demo beats](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_YCDemoBeats) address a prior persona-tailoring gap.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Assess_Tailoring_RevModel> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Assess_Tailoring_RevenueModelTAM> ;
